SIMPLE: not
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Not
<hw>Not</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Contr. from <ets>ne wot</ets>. See 2d
<er>Note</er>.]</ety> <def>Wot not; know not; knows not.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Not</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Not
<hw>Not</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Shorn; shaven.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <see>See <er>Nott</er>.</see>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Not</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Not
<hw>Not</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>not</ets>, <ets>noht</ets>,
<ets>nought</ets>, <ets>naught</ets>, the same word as E.
<ets>naught</ets>. See <er>Naught</er>.]</ety> <def>A word used to
express negation, prohibition, denial, or refusal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Not</qex> one word spake he more than was need.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou shalt <qex>not</qex> steal.</q> <rj><qau>Ex. xx.
15.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thine eyes are upon me, and I am <qex>not</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Job
vii. 8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The question is, may I do it, or may I <qex>not</qex> do it?</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Sanderson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Not . . . but</b></col>, <it>or</it> <col><b>Not
but</b></col></mcol>, <cd>only.</cd> <mark>[Obs. or Colloq.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Notabilia</ent>⟦br⟧
